Since Ms. Gao isn't here,

21
00:01:47,070 --> 00:01:48,770
I'll head out.

22
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:49,770
Come here.

23
00:01:55,150 --> 00:01:56,330
Shi...

24
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:58,260
Shi Wei?

25
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,020
I was drunk last night.
Sorry about that.

26
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:05,020
I've already spoken
to the director about the money.

27
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:05,850
I really

28
00:02:05,870 --> 00:02:06,770
put you in a tough spot last night.

29
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:07,740
Forgive me.

30
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,660
Please don't say that, Mr. Gao.

31
00:02:09,870 --> 00:02:11,170
I really didn't have the authority.

32
00:02:11,190 --> 00:02:13,450
Otherwise, I would've given you
the money last night.

33
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:16,610
How long have you been with the company?

34
00:02:18,190 --> 00:02:18,940
Almost half a year.

35
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,130
Half a year?

36
00:02:20,710 --> 00:02:21,540
My fault.

37
00:02:22,030 --> 00:02:23,450
I've been in Macao, China
for the past half a year.

38
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,850
I had no idea

39
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:26,660
there was someone named Shi Wei
in the Finance Department.

40
00:02:28,470 --> 00:02:29,170
How old are you?

41
00:02:30,030 --> 00:02:30,610
Twenty-two.

42
00:02:31,430 --> 00:02:33,260
Just graduated from college?

43
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:34,690
Yes.

44
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:36,340
Such a youthful age.

45
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:48,220
Come here.

46
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:49,850
Take this.

47
00:02:50,590 --> 00:02:52,410
What is this for?

48
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,450
I sincerely apologize

49
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,730
for my behavior last night.

50
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:00,850
Mr. Gao,

51
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,780
I really can't accept this.

52
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:04,410
You had too much to drink last night.

53
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:05,820
I'll just assume you were drunk.

54
00:03:06,870 --> 00:03:08,100
Just take it.

55
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:09,660
Mr. Gao, I really can't...

56
00:03:12,470 --> 00:03:12,940
Sorry.

57
00:03:33,430 --> 00:03:34,130
Are you okay?

58
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:36,060
I'm fine.

59
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,610
Can you drive faster?

60
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:44,450
Sorry.

61
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,850
What's the rush?

62
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,220
I have news about my dad.

63
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:09,980
Dad,

64
00:04:10,470 --> 00:04:11,100
have some water.

65
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:29,810
Dad,

66
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:32,410
I'll go buy some groceries.
Be right back.

67
00:05:16,070 --> 00:05:16,660
Dad.

68
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:19,290
Dad.

69
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:24,900
Dad!

70
00:05:41,980 --> 00:05:43,980
[Congratulations on
your successful interview.]

71
00:05:43,980 --> 00:05:45,260
[Queen Ballet welcomes you to join!]

72
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,340
This is the place.

73
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,290
What are you doing here?

74
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,580
Is this Tan Jun's place?

75
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:14,620
Yes.

76
00:06:14,910 --> 00:06:15,450
Who are you?

77
00:06:15,870 --> 00:06:16,770
I'm his daughter.

78
00:06:16,790 --> 00:06:17,450
I want to see him.

79
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,140
He's not home right now.

80
00:06:24,790 --> 00:06:25,580
What are you doing?

81
00:06:26,350 --> 00:06:27,450
This is their home. Stop making a scene.

82
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:28,940
It's their home.

83
00:06:31,110 --> 00:06:31,770
Alright.

84
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,260
How much money does your dad want?

85
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,820
What money?

86
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:37,650
What are you talking about, Mom?

87
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,650
Is he conspiring with that Shi Wei girl

88
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,770
to blackmail Haotian?

89
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:42,890
How much does he want?

90
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:44,770
What are you saying?

91
00:06:44,790 --> 00:06:45,820
How much money does he want?

92
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:46,330
Mom, that's enough.

93
00:06:46,350 --> 00:06:47,450
You need evidence to make such claims!

94
00:06:47,790 --> 00:06:48,500
Stop it, Mom.

95
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:50,820
Tell him

96
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:52,210
he's a murderer.

97
00:06:52,230 --> 00:06:52,890
Get out!

98
00:06:52,910 --> 00:06:53,380
Mom.

99
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:56,290
Mom, what are you doing?

100
00:06:58,280 --> 00:06:59,770
You told me you would talk properly.

101
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:19,620
I'm sorry.

102
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,290
I didn't know you were...

103
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:23,820
Murderer's daughter?

104
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:26,940
I apologize for what my mom said.

105
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:28,620
She's just very emotional right now.

106
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,140
I hope you can understand a little.

107
00:07:30,230 --> 00:07:31,090
I don't understand!

108
00:07:33,230 --> 00:07:34,530
Wei was the victim here.

109
00:07:34,550 --> 00:07:35,580
She was only twenty-two.

110
00:07:36,350 --> 00:07:37,410
That scum Gao Haotian...

111
00:07:37,430 --> 00:07:37,850
I know.

112
00:07:39,470 --> 00:07:39,850
I know.

113
00:07:44,430 --> 00:07:44,740
Also,

114
00:07:46,110 --> 00:07:47,740
why didn't you tell me

115
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:49,210
that Tianlu Trade
is your family's company?

116
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,890
Were you afraid
I was after your family's money?

117
00:07:52,350 --> 00:07:52,940
Of course not.

118
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:53,820
Why would you think that?

119
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:54,820
That's what your mom thinks.

120
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,330
My mom is not me.

121
00:08:02,110 --> 00:08:02,890
So you think

122
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,850
Gao Haotian's death
was my dad's fault, too?

123
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,930
His death was a result
of his own mistakes.

124
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,930
Ting, I'll talk to my mom

125
00:08:12,950 --> 00:08:14,020
and tell her not to bother your dad.

126
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,250
Believe me, alright?

127
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,780
What did my dad do wrong?

128
00:08:17,310 --> 00:08:18,700
What did Wei do wrong?

129
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:20,660
Why does your mom
want to cause trouble for my dad?

130
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,050
My mom just lost her family.

131
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:23,290
She's not thinking clearly right now.

132
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:24,850
Stop. Just go.

133
00:08:47,140 --> 00:08:48,790
[Congratulations on
your successful interview.]

134
00:08:48,790 --> 00:08:50,060
[Queen Ballet welcomes you to join!]

135
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:52,810
I'm going out for a walk.

136
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,020
Don't worry about me.

137
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:57,170
Hello?

138
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,100
Where are you guys?

139
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:01,740
Hurry up.

140
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:02,380
I know.

141
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:03,340
I'm on my way up.

142
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:05,460
I'm here.

143
00:09:06,590 --> 00:09:06,980
Ting!

144
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:11,930
I checked

145
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,860
all the usual streets
and our regular restaurants.

146
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:15,220
Nothing.

147
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:15,860
Nothing at all.

148
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:16,620
I looked too.

149
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:17,740
I asked everyone at the market.

150
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:18,620
No one said they'd seen him.

151
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:19,740
I even showed them his photo.

152
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:20,740
What about the company?

153
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:21,860
Did you go to the company?

154
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,050
He's not there either.

155
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:25,690
What should we do, Shuhan?

156
00:09:26,950 --> 00:09:27,810
Where could he have gone?

157
00:09:27,830 --> 00:09:28,410
Ting.

158
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:30,570
Let's call the police.

159
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:31,500
Right.

160
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,860
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

161
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:34,500
- You're welcome.
- Bye.

162
00:09:35,430 --> 00:09:36,170
Be careful on your way back.

163
00:09:38,310 --> 00:09:38,620
Ting,

164
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:39,930
don't panic just yet.

165
00:09:40,430 --> 00:09:41,340
The police said

166
00:09:41,590 --> 00:09:42,810
it hasn't been twenty-four hours.

167
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,170
We just have to wait for news.

168
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:44,740
Right.

169
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:45,860
Yuan,

170
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,570
let's take Ting home together.

171
00:09:47,590 --> 00:09:47,980
Okay.

172
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:52,860
What's wrong?

173
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:04,460
Are you sure this is the place?

174
00:10:04,710 --> 00:10:05,340
Should be here.

175
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:06,100
Thanks.

176
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:06,860
You can head back now.

177
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:07,860
Want me to go with you?

178
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:08,460
Don't bother.

179
00:10:34,710 --> 00:10:35,380
Ms. Tan?

180
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:39,100
Hello.

181
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:39,740
Hi.

182
00:10:40,430 --> 00:10:41,500
I'm the one who called.

183
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:43,810
My surname is Wang.

184
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:45,020
Just call me Wang.

185
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:48,140
You posted online

186
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:49,690
looking for your father, right?

187
00:10:49,950 --> 00:10:50,380
Yes.

188
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:52,340
It's quite a coincidence.

189
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:53,410
A while back, I was on a business trip

190
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,260
and saw a homeless man.

191
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:56,500
I thought

192
00:10:56,520 --> 00:10:59,220
his height and build
looked a lot like your father's.

193
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,810
Most importantly, I heard the locals

194
00:11:01,830 --> 00:11:03,500
call him Tan.

195
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:04,980
Tan

196
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:06,260
isn't a very common surname.

197
00:11:06,710 --> 00:11:07,860
So I thought

198
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:09,220
it was likely your father.

199
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:10,690
That's why I called you.

200
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:14,460
Where did you

201
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,140
see...

202
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:16,100
see my father?

203
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:18,500
I...

204
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:19,980
Well, you see,

205
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:22,740
I noticed your post mentioned

206
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:24,340
a reward, right?

207
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,220
Don't get me wrong.

208
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:28,810
I really shouldn't

209
00:11:29,830 --> 00:11:31,100
take the money.

210
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:32,860
After all, it's a good deed.

211
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:34,140
But

212
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,650
my family is struggling.

213
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:37,260
My wife doesn't work,

214
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:38,100
and my child is still young.

215
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:40,220
So I... I really need the money.

216
00:11:40,710 --> 00:11:43,860
So, could you give me the reward

217
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:44,980
first...?

218
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:46,860
Here's the thing, Mr. Wang.

219
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:48,860
I rushed over
as soon as I got your call.

220
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,340
I was in such a hurry.

221
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:52,570
I didn't bring much cash with me.

222
00:11:52,590 --> 00:11:55,100
But if the information you provide

223
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,340
confirms the man

224
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:57,570
is my father,

225
00:11:57,910 --> 00:11:59,570
I will definitely give you the reward.

226
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:04,620
Alright then.

227
00:12:04,830 --> 00:12:06,050
I... I'll trust you.

228
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:09,020
So here's what happened.

229
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,100
I was on a business trip.

230
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:12,100
One day, I was eating out.

231
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:13,340
It was really cold that day.

232
00:12:13,830 --> 00:12:14,740
A little snowy too.

233
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:17,100
A homeless man came into the restaurant.

234
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:18,890
The staff tried to kick him out.

235
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,460
They said, "Tan,

236
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:20,810
I've told you

237
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:21,860
so many times

238
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:23,380
not to come here.
Why are you back again?"

239
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,140
I thought he looked really pitiful.

240
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,500
He wasn't dressed warmly,

241
00:12:26,760 --> 00:12:28,140
and his lips were purple from the cold.

242
00:12:28,830 --> 00:12:30,500
I figured I'd ordered
too much food anyway.

243
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:32,620
So I shared some of my meal with him.

244
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:34,690
We ate together

245
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,570
and chatted a bit.

246
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:39,740
He said he'd been away from home
for a long time.

247
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:40,980
He hadn't gone back.

248
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:41,930
He missed home

249
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:43,620
and his daughter.

250
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:47,500
You're his only daughter, right?

251
00:12:48,590 --> 00:12:48,980
Yes.

252
00:12:50,310 --> 00:12:51,860
Then he must have been talking
about you.

253
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:53,050
Oh,

254
00:12:53,590 --> 00:12:56,260
and I noticed
he didn't seem to be in great shape.

255
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:58,930
His mind wasn't very clear.

256
00:12:58,950 --> 00:13:00,340
He was limping when he walked.

257
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:02,810
I wondered if he'd gotten hurt

258
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,100
while he was out there.

259
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:06,810
So you really need to find him quickly.

260
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:09,690
Had he been drinking?

261
00:13:09,710 --> 00:13:11,220
He usually gets like that
after he drinks.

262
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:13,620
Right.

263
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:15,620
At first, he wasn't drinking.

264
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:16,930
But then, while eating,

265
00:13:16,950 --> 00:13:18,460
he wanted a drink.

266
00:13:18,830 --> 00:13:20,500
It was cold.

267
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:22,380
So I bought him
a small bottle of baijiu.

268
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:23,740
But he didn't drink much.

269
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,860
If I'd known he would get like that,

270
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:26,810
I wouldn't have bought it for him.

271
00:13:26,830 --> 00:13:27,500
It's okay.

272
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:29,500
You meant well.

273
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:30,460
He

274
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:31,810
has been like this for years.

275
00:13:31,830 --> 00:13:34,100
And when he drinks,
he always talks about my mom.

276
00:13:37,310 --> 00:13:38,140
Exactly.

277
00:13:38,950 --> 00:13:41,220
After a few drinks, he told me a lot.

278
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,980
Especially about your mother.

279
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:47,460
Really.

280
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,810
I felt so bad for him.

281
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:51,980
He said it's tough

282
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:53,340
being out there alone.

283
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:55,140
He missed home,

284
00:13:55,590 --> 00:13:56,690
his wife,

285
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:58,100
and his daughter. Really.

286
00:13:58,480 --> 00:13:59,930
I... I felt sorry for him.

287
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,100
Mr. Wang,

288
